Text.Value: You are impatient. Even in this, you remind me of her, of Belynne Stelmane.
You have shown me great empathy. We are closer now, close enough - I hope - that I can ask you to reconsider your position regarding your physical form.
You remain very attached to your physical form. I suggest you shed it.

EditorData.logicalname: Noone partialillithid + Astral tadpole not destroyed

Text.Value: We are more alike than you would like to acknowledge. I am merely further along in my evolution than you.
I understand my outer membrane and appendages unnerve you. But despite my exterior, I still feel.
And yet you emulate it so well.
Give the Emperor's hand a reassuring squeeze.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [LILI] Player give Emperor a reassuring squeeze on their hand, from front
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player gives the Emperor's hand a squeeze with a look of ecnouragement. The mind flayer gives a look of gratitude.

Text.Value: Belynne, is it? The duke that's dead?
Trying to guard us. The brain is restless. But I'm distracted, and my lack of focus is endangering us.
I won't.
Your company isn't unwelcome.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Awkward silence before the Emperor speaks.
The emperor gives a sage, knowing nod.

Text.Value: I appreciate the offer, but I don't think it will help.
What are you doing?
But unlike you, unlike the others of my kind, I am no slave to either.
Do you need another hug?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [LILI] *REUSE* [Player] CINE_Slow_Walk_to_Stop, [Emperor] Seated looking into the distance Idle
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player wakes up in the dream field. Shot of the Emperor is sitting with its back to you on a bench, alone, looking unusually pensive and morose against the backdrop of the astral plane - the globe of domination visible in the distance. All is quiet now in contrast to the battles we previously saw here. The player approaches.

Text.Value: I really don't care what your relationship with her was like.
Most people think that mind flayers are soulless husks who feel nothing. I am glad you are not most people.
Apology accepted.
My end is and has always been freedom.
If I didn't know you were a mind flayer, I'd say you were upset.
I could not have done any of it without her. Just as I cannot do any of this without you. But now she's gone.

EditorData.NodeContext: voice slightly breaking, as if on the verge of tears

Text.Value: *You feel the Emperor's fear as if it were your own. An elder brain enslaved is one thing, an elder brain unleashed will be the end of everything.*
Drop the act. I know you don't have feelings.
Very well. Then let us move on.
Do you need a hug?
You would do well to be more like me. Now leave.
Don't let your guard down again.
Once those orders are complete, there is a good chance it will break free.
In life, she was my business partner. Back when we ran the Knights of the Shield. A difficult task, for a mind flayer.
Belynne understood this. Belynne became my freedom.
We will do better against the elder brain the more illithid we both are.
Far from it. I have long sought the allyship of others - it is the only way to succeed.
I am glad you were able to learn something.
Who do you think of?
I appreciate your understanding.
Another quake. The brain is rebelling again. I need to focus. And so do you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Brain quake. The Emperor pulls itself together and straightens to its full height, back in business. The player stands also.
EditorData.NodeContext: Emperor stands up and look around at the furniture disappearing around him. Calm & collected

Text.Value: You seem troubled.
Was it more... intimate?
You are weaker than I imagined, if you lie to yourself so.
I just want a dreamless sleep for once.
Like you, mind flayers know fear. Like you, we crave recognition.
I know it is no easy choice for you, but we will have a far better time ridding the city of Gortash if you accept just a touch of illithidness.
I need to focus. The brain is rebelling again. Be on your way and leave me to my thoughts.
Come, you may as well sit a while, now that you're here.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Emperor pats the spot on the bench next to him. Player sits beside Emperor.
EditorData.NodeContext: Emperor looks to his right at player

Text.Value: An accurate summary. I have found myself distracted of late.
Your company is disgusting.
Its rebellion against Orin and Gortash has been fierce. Even as it executes their final orders.
And yet you hurt them.
Beautiful, isn't it? The mighty Prince Orpheus, contained in submissive slumber.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Closer shot of globe of domination and skull vista.

Text.Value: You would do well to be more like me. Your humanoid tendencies are becoming an encumbrance. Leave me.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Emperor sat on bench. Player stood next to him. Shot from behind of the two them looking out at the view together.

Text.Value: I expected you to be more on guard this close to the brain.
I see you are unable to let that go. But do not forget that I trusted you with my life, as you trusted me with yours.
It was she who met with the merchants, politicians, patriars. It was she who negotiated deals and signed off on agreements. Her rooms played host to the most important conversations in the city.
At least - when she was alive.
Not to mention the elder brain itself. Our chances against it greatly improve the more illithid we both are.
But I could do with your assistance. You remain attached to your physical form. I suggest you shed that attachment.
You thought you were my first ally?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player reacts with surprise at the longing in the Emperor's voice when it talks of Stelmane. Emperor clocks our surprise.

Text.Value: Watching your loves die only makes you tougher.
Forgive me. I am drained. Ever since you killed Ketheric and took his Netherstone, the Chosen's control of the brain has been... brittle.
Did you manipulate her like you manipulated me?
I'm sorry for your loss.

EditorData.stateContext: Player sitting. Emperor sitting. Player seated on Emperor's right

Text.Value: Someone from your past?
That was... insightful.
I suspected that when we took Ketheric's stone, the brain would begin to break free. Those brainquakes confirm that my suspicion was correct.
What I feel is deeper than superficial cures can reach. And not entirely unwelcome.
The very same. Duke Stelmane, as she was known in Baldur's Gate.
I do not know what happens now when it receives their orders, and I do not dare guess.
Manipulation or not, we need each other. My relationship with Belynne was similar in this regard. Though - less dramatic.
Not love, no. What I had with Belynne Stelmane was much more than that. It was - unique.
The past is past. Move on.
Indeed. Duke Stelmane. Or as I knew her - Belynne. When she was alive.
In a way. But not the way you're thinking of.
Thank you for sharing that.
Astute as ever.
I know you're trying to manipulate me. It's not working. I know what you are.
Though my relationship with Belynne was - different, from my relationship with you.
You have a love interest?
How did you - oh. It's you. I must have let my mind wander. Enough for you to wander in.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player wakes up in the dream field. Shot of the Emperor is sitting with its back to you on a bench, alone, looking unusually pensive and morose against the backdrop of the astral plane - the globe of domination visible in the distance. All is quiet now in contrast to the battles we previously saw here. The player approaches. The Emperor notices us with a start - they weren't expecting us.
EditorData.NodeContext: Emperor startled by player, looks behind to his right, before looking back infront

Text.Value: I'm haunted by memories. They are relentless. I can think of nothing - no one - else.
*As your eyes blink shut, you fall into the deepest slumber of your life. A quietness so vast it feels almost like death.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player's eyes fall shut. Fade to black.

Text.Value: Another quake. The brain is rebelling again. I need to focus.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Brain quake. The Emperor pulls itself together and straightens to its full height, back in business. The player stands also.
EditorData.NodeContext: Emperor stands up and look around at the furniture disappearing around him. Calm & collected

Text.Value: Sorry I was mean to you.
Together, we brought order to chaos. At its height, everything that happened in that city went through the Shield. Through us.
Duke Stelmane trusted me, and the city trusted her. I conceived the plot, but Belynne took centre-stage.
You are wrong. Feeling is vital to the pursuit of anyone's goals. Even a mind flayer's.
You are correct. I should be.
You think that mind flayers are soulless husks who feel nothing. Belynne thought the same at first.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player gives mind flayer a skeptical look.

Text.Value: How so?
Duke Stelmane. Or Belynne, as I knew her. I wasn't ready for her death.
I apologise. I didn't mean to burden you with my woes. You have enough to worry about.
It's rebelling against Orin and Gortash. Fiercely.

Synopsis: Upon our learning of Stelmanes murder, we stumble on the Emperor in a dream, reflecting nostalgically on its past life with Stelmane and all that it hopes to reclaim (all part of the mind flayer manipulation).
